item.title: Minecraft: Ghosts n' Stuff by DeadMau5 (Note Block Remix)
item.description:
Minecraft: Ghosts n' Stuff by DeadMau5 (Note Block Remix)
As you can probably tell, this was a pretty involved project. That being said, if you enjoyed watching and listening, it would be awesome if you could take half a second to rate/favorite; it helps other users find the video who might not have otherwise. Also, thanks to those of you who shared this with DeadMau5. He actually ended up watching it :) This was created only with the sounds from Minecraft's newly introduced "note blocks." Over the second half of the video, I also played the original "Ghosts n' Stuff" track quietly in the background, as I thought it made for a cool effect and a bit more varied sound. While some minor audio filters, along the lines of reverb and equalizer, were used in Vegas to enhance the sound of the note blocks, absolutely NO pitch adjustment nor autotune was used. The notes you hear in the video are all the actual notes from the game. Hence, a few might be missing due to the two octave limit. DeadMau5 also has a YouTube channel and plays Minecraft himself :) http://www.youtube.com/deadmau5 For those of you asking about the mods/texture packs used, the links can be found below. For the in game DeadMau5 paintings, I manually edited the art file in Photoshop. http://www.minecraftforum.net/viewtopic.php?t=55700 http://www.minecraftforum.net/viewtopic.php?f=1021&t=73861

item.title: Chic Sophisticated Hair
item.description:
Chic Sophisticated Hair
Hey bubbiful ones! Time for another hair tutorial. I'll demonstrate step by step how to create Chic & Sophisticated hair. I often see singers, models and famous actresses in HK, S.Korea or even in Europe wear their hair in huge quiffs/poofs. The added height makes the face appear sharper and slimmer (believe it or not). I demonstrate 4 possible hairstyles which are all sophisticated, sassy and edgy. One particular style is inspired by Sandara from 2NE1. You guys don't see me show my entire face often because I have a high forehead and I do have a round face lol. Therefore I have always been self conscious I guess. However, my mum always tells me to clip my fringe up because I look fresher and more awake. We will always be our own harsh critics. She is right tho- you will def look more fresh-faced with these hairstyles because your cheekbones will stand out. This is probably the ONLY tutorial where I really 'tease' my hair. You guys can understand why. I don't like teasing my hair often because it just isn't good for the hair. I recommend teasing hair for special occasions only. Again- shoutout to awesome instrumental creator "GPBeatz" for awesome instrumental of 'Soom' by Beast. Hope you guys enjoy this quickie! Take care and I'll speak to you soonie!! Much love, Bubz xx Follow me on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/bubzbeauty Bubzbeauty Official Website: http://www.bubzbeauty.com Shop the Bubbi Clothing Line: http://bubbi.bubzbeauty.com Connect with me at the Bubzbeauty Fanpage where I chill n catch up with you guys ^^ http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bubzbeauty-Official/181811348879
